"{\"uid\": \"lbc.co.uk-article-worms-in-food-at-the-olympic-village-adam-peaty-slams-paris-2024-catering-5HjcpDb_2\", \"text\": \"By Henry Moore  Team GB swimmer Adam Peaty has slammed the catering available at Paris 2024, claiming some athletes have found worms in their meals at the Olympic Village.  This comes after Peaty finished fourth in 4x100m medley relay on the final evening of swimming at the 2024 games.  In a bid to meet sustainability pledges organisers have aimed to make 60 per cent of all meals served meatless and a third plant-based, much to Peaty\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s disappointment.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe catering isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t good enough for the level the athletes are expected to perform. We need to give the best we possibly can,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the silver-medal-winning swimmer told the publication,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009dhe told the i.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTokyo, the food was incredible, Rio was incredible. But this time around [\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6] there wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t enough protein options, long queues, waiting 30 minutes for food because there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s no queuing system.  Read more:Olympic swimmer speaks out over 'lies' after being banned from athletes village for 'inappropriate conduct'  Read More:Olympic swimmer Luana Alonso removed from Athletes' Village over claims she created an 'inappropriate environment'  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThese [complaints] are for people to get better. And the organising committee, so we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll put these back to our team in full depth and detail.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBut it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s definitely been the best Games in terms of fans engaged with it. So you never gonna have a perfect Games.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  A Paris 2024 spokesperson told the i: \\\"We are listening to the athletes and take their feedback very seriously.  \\\"Since the opening of the village, our partner Sodexo Live! has been working proactively to adapt supplies to the growing use of the Olympic Village restaurants, as well as to the actual consumption by athletes observed over the first few days.  \\\"As a result, the quantities of certain products has been significantly increased and additional staff have been deployed to ensure the service runs smoothly.\\\"  Peaty slammed organisers for a lack of protein options and even claimed some athletes have found worms in their fish.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe narrative of sustainability has just been punished on the athletes. I want to meat, I need meat to perform and that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s what I eat at home, so why should I change?\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Peaty continued.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI like my fish and people are finding worms in the fish. It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just not good enough.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe standard, we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re looking at the best of the best in the world, and we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re feeding them not the best.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI just want people to get better at their roles and jobs. And I think that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s what the athletes are the best sounding board for.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  This isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t the first complaint Peaty, who is recovering from Covid, has expressed about Paris 2024.  Olympic organisers told LBC that no reports of worms in food have been made by Team GB athletes.  Yesterday, he hit out at the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cbizarre\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d anti-doping rules that allowed two Chinese athletes who allegedly took banned substances to compete in the 4x100m medley relay, winning gold.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe have to be very careful not to paint a whole nation with one brush, firstly,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Peaty told LBC\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Charlotte Lynch.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBut also, that we kind of set a punishment, or set a barrier for those people who are cheating and it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s very blatant.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cGiving each nation their own responsibility and trust in that nation to test their own athletes \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s bizarre.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe should have a full de-centralised testing agency that tests everyone fairly.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI want to play fair, I swim fair, I know how hard I worked to get here.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The use of the Ajax vehicle was halted for two weeks to allow an investigation to be carried out  1h ago  The Home Secretary and Foreign Secretary said they had reached \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009can arrangement\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d with the Chinese government on \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cconsolidating\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Beijing\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s diplomatic presence in one site  1h ago  The former 'I am A Celebrity' contestant told followers she was suffering from inflammation all over her body  2h ago  The star told fans he had been dealing with a \\\"lot of health issues over the last year\\\"  3h ago  The Supreme Court ruling said the words \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cwoman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009csex\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d in the Equality Act 2010 refer to a biological woman and biological sex  4h ago  Disney fans confused as to why animation needed different titles across the Atlantic  4h ago  With his side losing 17-7 to the New England Patriots on Monday, Koo lined up a 47-yard field goal attempt, as he had done many times before  4h ago  The use of the Ajax vehicle was halted for two weeks to allow an investigation to be carried out  1h ago  The Home Secretary and Foreign Secretary said they had reached \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009can arrangement\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d with the Chinese government on \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cconsolidating\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Beijing\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s diplomatic presence in one site  1h ago  The Supreme Court ruling said the words \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cwoman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009csex\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d in the Equality Act 2010 refer to a biological woman and biological sex  4h ago  The officers made \\\"concerted efforts\\\"  to blame fans in the aftermath  5h ago  A 'quality issue' with metal fuselage panels on multiple\\u00c2\\u00a0A320 models has been discovered.  6h ago  A dozen prisoners have been mistakenly freed in the past month with two remaining at large.  8h ago  Other big name actors such as Dame Judi Dench and Brian Cox are also supporting Age UK's campaign against loneliness.  9h ago  Follow us:  About & Help  Get The LBC App  Legal & Info  Business & Careers  \\u00c2\\u00a9 Global 2025 | 30 Leicester Square, London, WC2H 7LA  Copyright Global 2025. 30 Leicester Square, London. W C 2 H 7 L A.\"}"